Built on the Stash memory engine
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Motion Memory Core is a deployment, gateway, transport, and integration layer.
The underlying memory engine is Stash, an independent open-source project:

    Stash — https://github.com/alash3al/stash
    Copyright (c) the Stash authors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

This repository does NOT vendor Stash's source code. It runs Stash as a
dependency (built from source or pulled as an image) and adds its own
MIT-licensed components around it:

  - a native Streamable HTTP transport (contributed upstream to Stash),
  - a bearer-auth gateway,
  - one-click / self-host deployment recipes,
  - multi-client connection integrations and documentation.

Any distribution that includes Stash's source or binaries remains subject to
the Apache License 2.0 for those portions. See:
https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0
